    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/adobo-inspired-crispy-chicken-and-pineapple-brown-rice-bowl/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cut your<strong> chicken breast strips</strong> into bite-sized pieces, then add to a bowl with your <strong>cornflour</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and give everything a good mix up until the chicken is coated in the flour</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick, with a matching lid), over a high heat with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated chicken </strong>and<strong> </strong>cook for 10-12 min or until the chicken is crispy, browned all over and cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/adobo-inspired-crispy-chicken-and-pineapple-brown-rice-bowl/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice your <strong>shallot[s] </strong>thinly</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Remove your<strong> pineapple</strong> from the can (save the juice!) and chop roughly</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/adobo-inspired-crispy-chicken-and-pineapple-brown-rice-bowl/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong> finely</p><p>Wash your <strong>lettuce</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper and roughly shred</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/adobo-inspired-crispy-chicken-and-pineapple-brown-rice-bowl/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add a splash of<strong> </strong>the <strong>reserved pineapple juice </strong>to a small bowl with your <strong>mayo</strong> and stir it all together \u2013 this is your <strong>pineapple mayo</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/adobo-inspired-crispy-chicken-and-pineapple-brown-rice-bowl/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Transfer the cooked chicken to a plate and return the pan to medium heat with a small drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>pineapple</strong> and<strong> shallot </strong>and<strong> </strong>cook for 2-3 min or until softening</p><p>Once softening, add your <strong>gluten free soy sauce</strong>,<strong> remaining pineapple juice</strong> and your<strong> cider vinegar </strong>and cook for a final 1-2 min or until thickened</p><p>Once thickened, add the <strong>crispy chicken</strong> to the pan and toss to coat \u2013 this is your <strong>adobo-inspired crispy chicken & pineapple</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/adobo-inspired-crispy-chicken-and-pineapple-brown-rice-bowl/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add most of the <strong>chopped spring onion</strong> (save some for garnish) to the cooked rice with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and stir it all together \u2013 this is your <strong>spring onion rice</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/adobo-inspired-crispy-chicken-and-pineapple-brown-rice-bowl/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> adobo-inspired crispy chicken & pineapple </strong>with the <strong>spring onion rice</strong> and <strong>shredded lettuce</strong> to the side</p><p>Drizzle the lettuce with the <strong>pineapple mayo</strong></p><p>Garnish with the<strong> remaining sliced spring onion</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
